This directory contains files to test fvwm2 (no modules) for memory leaks.

Instructions:

 - execute the shell script purify.install to copy some files needed by
   the config file to /tmp
 - edit purify.fvwm2rc so that the correct ModulePath is included in the
   last ModulePath statement (all in one block)
 - copy purify.fvwm2rc over your .fvwm2rc (or execute it any way you like)
 - (re)start fvwm
 - wait until the six windows have been created and the cursor warps near the
   lower right edge of the screen; the windows redraw and the setup halts;
   now press mouse button 2 to proceed.
 - whenever fvwm2 expects user input, press mouse button 1
 - the script will ternimate itself

NOTE: you can safely ignore all error messages, beeps, ...
   


